obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (33028)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33028&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Central Sales Tax Act,`
  line 1956.
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 5 of 1958, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `2. 5th January, 1957, all sections except section 15, vide notification No. S.R.O. 78, dated 4th January, 1957, Gazette of India,`
  line `Extra. 1957, Pt. II, Section 3, p.57; and section 15 with effect from 1st October, 1958, vide G.S.R. 897, dated 23rd September,`
  line `1958, Gazette of India, Extra. 1958, Pt. II, Section 3 (i), p. 476`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (33029)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33029&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appropriate State" means--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a dealer who has one or more places of business situate in the same`
  line `State, that State;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a dealer who has ^1*** places of business situate in the different States,`
  line `every such State with respect to the place or places of business situated within its territory;`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `^3[(aa) "business" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) any trade, commerce or manufacture, or any adventure or concern in the nature of`
  line `trade, commerce or manufacture, whether or not such trade, commerce,`
  line `manufacture, adventure or concern is carried on with a motive to make gain or profit and`
  line `whether or not any gain or profit accrues from such trade, commerce, manufacture,`
  line `adventure or concern; and`
  line
  line `(ii) any transaction in connection with or incidental or ancillary to, such trade,`
  line `commerce, manufacture, adventure or concern;`
  line
  line `(ab) "crossing the customs frontiers of India" means crossing in the limits of the area of a`
  line `customs station in which imported goods or export goods are ordinarily kept before clearance`
  line `by customs authorities.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, "customs station" and "customs authorities" shall`
  line `have the same meanings as in the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962);`
  line
  line `^4[(b) "dealer" means any person who carries on (whether regularly or otherwise) the business of`
  line `buying, selling, supplying or distributing goods, directly or indirectly, for cash or for deferred payment,`
  line `or for commission remuneration or other valuable consideration, and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a local authority, a body corporate, a company, any co-operative society or`
  line `other society, club, firm, Hindu undivided family or other association of persons`
  line `which carries on such business;`
  line
  line `(ii) a factor, broker, commission agent, del credere agent, or any other mercantile agent,`
  line `by whatever name called, and whether of the same description as hereinbefore mentioned or`
  line `not, who carries on the business of buying, selling, supplying or distributing, goods belonging`
  line `to any principal whether disclosed or not; and`
  line
  line `(iii) an auctioneer who carries on the business of selling or auctioning goods belonging to`
  line `any principal, whether disclosed or not and whether the offer of the intending purchaser is`
  line `accepted by him or by the principal or a nominee of the principal.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--Every person who acts as an agent, in any State, of a dealer residing outside`
  line `that State and buys, sells, supplies, or distributes, goods in the State or acts on behalf of such`
  line `dealer as--`
  line
  line `(i) a mercantile agent as defined in the Sale of Goods Act, 1930 (3 of 1930), or`
  line
  line `(ii) an agent for handling of goods or documents of title relating to goods, or`
  line
  line `(iii) an agent for the collection or the payment of the sale price of goods or as a`
  line `guarantor for such collection or payment,`
  line
  line `and every local branch or office in a State of a firm registered outside that State or a company or`
  line `other body corporate, the principal office or headquarters whereof is outside that State, shall be`
  line `deemed to be a dealer for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--A Government which, whether or not in the course of business, buy, sells,`
  line `supplies or distributes, goods, directly or otherwise, for cash or for deferred payment or for`
  line `commission, remuneration or other valuable consideration, shall except in relation to any sale,`
  line `supply or distribution or surplus, un-serviceable or old stores or materials or waste products or`
  line `obsolete or discarded machinery or parts or accessories thereof, be deemed to be a dealer for the`
  line `purposes of this Act;]`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `^6[(d) "goods" means--`
  line
  line `(i) petroleum crude;`
  line
  line `(ii) high speed diesel;`
  line
  line `(iii) motor spirit (commonly known as petrol);`
  line
  line `(iv) natural gas;`
  line
  line `(v) aviation turbine fuel; and`
  line
  line `(vi) alcoholic liquor for human consumption;]`
  line
  line `^7[(dd) "place of business" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) in any case where a dealer carries on business through an agent by (whatever`
  line `name called), the place of business of such agent;`
  line
  line `(ii) a warehouse, go down or other place where a dealer stores his goods; and`
  line
  line `(iii) a place where a dealer keeps his books of account;]`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "registered dealer" means a dealer who is registered under section 7;`
  line
  line `^8[(g) "sale", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means any transfer of`
  line `property in goods by one person to another for cash or deferred payment or for any other valuable`
  line `consideration, and includes,--`
  line
  line `(i) a transfer, otherwise than in pursuance of a contract, of property in any goods for cash,`
  line `deferred payment or other valuable consideration;`
  line
  line `(ii) a transfer of property in goods (whether as goods or in some other form) involved in the`
  line `execution of a works contract;`
  line
  line `(iii) a delivery of goods on hire-purchase or any system of payment by installments;`
  line
  line `(iv) a transfer of the right to use any goods for any purpose (whether or not for a specified`
  line `period) for cash, deferred payment or other valuable consideration;`
  line
  line `(v) a supply of goods by any unincorporated association or body of persons to a member`
  line `thereof for cash, deferred payment or other valuable consideration;`
  line
  line `(vi) a supply, by way of or as part of any service or in any other manner whatsoever, of`
  line `goods, being food or any other article for human consumption or any drink (whether or not`
  line `intoxicating), where such supply or service, is for cash, deferred payment or other valuable`
  line consideration,
  line
  line `but does not include a mortgage or hypothecation of or a charge or pledge on goods;]`
  line
  line `(h) "sale price" means the amount payable to a dealer as consideration for the sale of any`
  line `goods, less any sum allowed as cash discount according to the practice normally prevailing in the`
  line `trade, but inclusive of any sum charged for anything done by the dealer in respect of the goods at`
  line `the time of or before the delivery thereof other than the cost of freight or delivery or the cost of`
  line `installation in cases where such cost is separately charged:`
  line
  line `^9[Provided that in the case of a transfer of property in goods (whether as goods or in some other`
  line `form) involved in the execution of a works contract, the sale price of such goods shall be`
  line `determined in the prescribed manner by making such deduction from the total consideration for the`
  line `works contract as may be prescribed and such price shall be deemed to be the sale price for the`
  line `purposes of this clause.]`
  line
  line ^10
  line `[(i) "sales tax law" means any law for the time being in force in any State or part thereof which`
  line `provides for the levy of taxes on the sale or purchase of goods generally or on any specified goods`
  line `expressly mentioned in that behalf, and "general sales tax law" means the law for the time being in`
  line `force in any State or part thereof which provides for the levy of tax on the sale or purchase of goods`
  line `generally and includes value added tax law;]`
  line
  line `(j) "turnover" used in relation to any dealer liable to tax under this Act means the aggregate of the`
  line `sale prices received and receivable by him in respect of sales of any goods in the course of inter-State`
  line `trade or commerce made during any prescribed period ^11[and determined in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder;]`
  line
  line `^12[(ja) "works contract" means a contract for carrying out any work which included assembling,`
  line `construction, building, altering, manufacturing, processing, fabrication, erection, installation, fitting`
  line `out, improvement, repair or commissioning of any movable or immovable property;]`
  line
  line `(k) "year", in relation to a dealer, means the year applicable in relation to him under the general`
  line `sales tax law of the appropriate State, and where there is no such year applicable, the financial year.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "one or more" omitted by Act 31 of 1958, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `2. The Explanation omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 103 of 1976, s. 2 (w.e.f. 7-9-1076).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 103 of 1976, s. 2, for cl. (b) (w.e.f. 7-9-1976).`
  line
  line `5 Clause (c) omitted by Act 18 of 2017, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 18 of 2017, s. 13, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 31 of 1958, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 150, for clause (g) (w.e.f. 11-5-2002).`
  line
  line `9. The proviso ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 89 (w.e.f. 13-5-2005).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by s. 89, ibid., for clause (i) (w.e.f. 13-5-2005).`
  line
  line `11 Subs. by Act 28 of 1969, s. 2, for "and determined in the prescribed manner" (w.e.f. 30-8-1969).`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 89 (w.e.f. 13-5-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (33030)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `When is a sale or purchase of goods said to take place in the course of inter-State trade or commerce.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 224 (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33030&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `A sale or purchase of goods shall be deemed to take place in the course of inter-State`
  line `trade or commerce if the sale or purchase--`
  line
  line `(a) occasions the movement of goods from one State to another; or`
  line
  line `(b) is effected by a transfer of documents of title to the goods during their movement from`
  line `one State to another.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--Where goods are delivered to a carrier or other bailee for transmission, the`
  line `movement of the goods shall, for the purposes of clause (b), be deemed to commence at the time`
  line `of such delivery and terminate at the time when delivery is taken from such carrier or bailee.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--Where the movement of goods commences and terminates in the same State`
  line `it shall not be deemed to be a movement of goods from one State to another by reason merely of`
  line `the fact that in the course of such movement the goods pass through the territory of any other`
  line State.
  line
  line `^1[Explanation 3.--Where the gas sold or purchased and transported through a common`
  line `carrier pipeline or any other common transport or distribution system becomes co-mingled and`
  line `fungible with other gas in the pipeline or system and such gas is introduced into the pipeline or`
  line `system in one State and is taken out from the pipeline in another State, such sale or purchase of`
  line `gas shall be deemed to be a movement of goods from one State to another.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (33031)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `When is a sale or purchase of goods said to take place outside a State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33031&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the`
  line `provisions contained in section 3, when a sale or purchase of goods is determined in accordance with`
  line `sub-section (2) to take place inside a State, such sale or purchase shall be deemed to have taken place`
  line `outside all other States.`
  line
  line `(2) A sale or purchase of goods shall be deemed to take place inside a State, if the goods are within`
  line `the State--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of specific or ascertained goods, at the time the contract of sale is made; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of unascertained or future goods, at the time of their appropriation to the contract`
  line `of sale by the seller or by the buyer, whether assent of the other party is prior or subsequent to such`
  line appropriation
  line
  line `Explanation.--Where there is a single contract of sale or purchase of goods situated at more`
  line `places than one, the provisions of this sub-section shall apply as if there were separate contracts in`
  line `respect of the goods at each of such places.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (33032)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `When is a sale or purchase of goods said to take place in the course of import or export.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33032&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `A sale or purchase of goods shall be deemed to take place in the course of the export of the goods out of`
  line `the territory of India only if the sale or purchase either occasions such export or is effected by a transfer of`
  line `documents of title to the goods after the goods have crossed the customs frontiers of India.`
  line
  line `(2) A sale or purchase of goods shall be deemed to take place in the course of the import of the goods`
  line `into the territory of India only if the sale or purchase either occasions such import or is effected by a`
  line `transfer of documents of title to the goods before the goods have crossed the customs frontiers of India.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the last sale or purchase of any goods`
  line `preceding the sale or purchase occasioning the export of those goods out of the territory of India shall also`
  line `be deemed to be in the course of such export, if such last sale or purchase took place after, and was for the`
  line `purpose of complying with, the agreement or order for or in relation to such export.]`
  line
  line `^2[(4) The provisions of sub-section (3) shall not apply to any sale or purchase of goods unless the`
  line `dealer selling the goods furnishes to the prescribed authority in the prescribed manner a declaration duly`
  line `filled and signed by the exporter to whom the goods are sold in a prescribed form obtained from the`
  line `prescribed authority.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), if any designated Indian carrier purchases`
  line `Aviation Turbine Fuel for the purposes of its international flight, such purchase shall be deemed to take`
  line `place in the course of the export of goods out of the territory of India.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "designated Indian carrier" means any carrier`
  line `which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 103 of 1976, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 90 (w.e.f. 13-5-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (33033)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Liability to tax on inter-State sales.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33033&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Subject to the other provisions contained in this Act,`
  line `every dealer shall, with effect from such date as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, not being earlier than thirty days from the date of such notification, be liable to`
  line `pay tax under this Act on all sales ^2[of goods other than electrical energy] effected by him in the course of`
  line `inter- State trade or commerce during any year on and from the date so notified:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that a dealer shall not be liable to pay tax under this Act on any sale of goods which, in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-section (3) of section 5 is a sale in the course of export of those`
  line `goods out of the territory of India.]`
  line
  line `^4[(1A) A dealer shall be liable to pay tax under this Act on a sale of any goods effected by him in the`
  line `course of inter-State trade or commerce notwithstanding that no tax would have been leviable (whether on`
  line `the seller or the purchaser) under the sales tax law of the appropriate State if that sale had taken place`
  line `inside that State.]`
  line
  line `^5[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (1A), where a sale of any`
  line `goods in the course of inter-State trade or commerce has either occasioned the movement of such goods`
  line `from one State to another or has been effected toy a transfer of documents of title to such goods during`
  line `their movement from one State to another, any subsequent sale during such movement effected by a`
  line `transfer of documents of title to such goods to a registered dealer, if the goods are of the description`
  line `referred to in sub-section (3) of section 8, shall be exempt from tax under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such subsequent sale shall be exempt from tax under this sub-section unless the`
  line `dealer effecting the sale furnishes to the prescribed authority in the prescribed manner and within the`
  line `prescribed time or within such further time as that authority may, for sufficient cause, permit,--`
  line
  line `(a) a certificate duly filled and signed by the registered dealer from whom the goods were`
  line `purchased containing the prescribed particulars in a prescribed form obtained from the prescribed`
  line `authority; and`
  line
  line `(b) if the subsequent sale is made to a registered dealer, a declaration referred to in sub-section (4)`
  line `of section 8:`
  line
  line `Provided further that it shall not be necessary to furnish the declaration referred to in clause (b) of the`
  line `preceding proviso in respect of a subsequent sale of goods if,--`
  line
  line `(a) the sale or purchase of such goods is, under the sales tax law of the appropriate State exempt`
  line `from tax generally or is subject to tax generally at a rate which is lower than three per cent. or such`
  line `reduced rate as may be notified by the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 8 (whether called a tax or fee or by any other name); and`
  line
  line `(b) the dealer effecting such subsequent sale proves to the satisfaction of the authority referred to`
  line `in the preceding proviso that such sale is of the nature referred to in this sub-section.]`
  line
  line `^6[(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, if--`
  line
  line `(a) any official or personnel of--`
  line
  line `(i) any foreign diplomatic mission or consulate in India; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the United Nations or any other similar international body, entitled to privileges under any`
  line `convention to which India is a party or under any law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(b) any consular or diplomatic agent of any mission, the United Nations or other body referred to`
  line `in sub-clause (i) or sub-clause (ii) of clause (a), purchases any goods for himself or for the purposes`
  line `of such mission, United Nations or other body, then, the Central Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, exempt, subject to such conditions as may be specified in the notification, the tax`
  line `payable on the sale of such goods under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 6 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 31 of 1958, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 61 of 1972, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line
  line `3 Ins. by Act 103 of 1976, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 28 of 1969, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30-8-1969).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 16 of 2007, s. 2, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 16 of 2007, s. 2, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (33034)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 7
  title `Burden of proof, etc., in case of transfer of goods claimed otherwise than by way of sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33034&sectionno=6A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Burden of proof, etc., in case of transfer of goods claimed otherwise than by way of`
  line `sale.--(1) Where any dealer claims that he is not liable to pay tax under this Act, in respect of any goods,`
  line `on the ground that the movement of such goods from one State to another was occasioned by reason of`
  line `transfer of such goods by him to any other place of his business or to his agent or principal, as the case`
  line `may be, and not by reason of sale, the burden of proving that the movement of those goods was so`
  line `occasioned shall be on that dealer and for this purpose he may furnish to the assessing authority, within`
  line `the prescribed time or within such further time as that authority may, for sufficient cause, permit, a`
  line `declaration, duly filled and signed by the principal officer of the other place of business, or his agent or`
  line `principal, as the case may be, containing the prescribed particulars in the prescribed form obtained from`
  line `the prescribed authority, along with the evidence of dispatch of such goods ^2[, and if the dealer fails to`
  line `furnish such declaration, then, the movement of such goods shall be deemed for all purposes of this Act to`
  line `have been occasioned as a result of sale].`
  line
  line `(2) If the assessing authority is satisfied after making such inquiry as he may deem necessary that the`
  line `particulars contained in the declaration furnished by a dealer under sub-section (1)`
  line `^3[are true and that no`
  line `inter-State sale has been effected, he may, at the time of, or at any time before, the assessment of the tax`
  line `payable by the dealer under this Act, make an order to that effect and thereupon the movement of goods`
  line `to which the declaration relates shall, subject to the provisions of sub-section (3),] be deemed for the`
  line `purpose of this Act to have been occasioned otherwise than as a result of sale.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, "assessing authority", in relation to dealer, means the authority for the`
  line `time being competent to assess the tax payable by the dealer under this Act.`
  line
  line `^4[(3) Nothing contained in sub-section (2) shall preclude reassessment by the assessing authority on`
  line `the ground of discovery of new facts or revision by a higher authority on the ground that the findings of`
  line `the assessing authority are contrary to law, and such reassessment or revision may be done in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of general sales tax law of the State.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 61 of 1972, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 151 (w.e.f. 13-05-2002).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 78, for certain words (w.e.f. 8-5-2010).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 78, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-5-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (33035)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Registration of dealers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33035&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every dealer liable to pay tax under this Act shall, within such time`
  line `as may be prescribed for the purpose, make an application for registration under this Act to such authority`
  line `in the appropriate State as the Central Government may, by general or special order, specify, and every`
  line `such application shall contain such particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Any dealer who is liable to pay tax under the sales tax law of the appropriate State or where`
  line `there is no such law in force in the appropriate State or any part thereof, any dealer having a place of`
  line `business in that State or part, as the case may be, may, notwithstanding that he is not liable to pay tax`
  line `under this Act, apply for registration under this Act to the authority referred to in sub-section (1), and`
  line `every such application shall contain such particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, a dealer shall be deemed to be liable to pay tax`
  line `under the sales tax law of the appropriate state notwithstanding that under such law a sale or purchase`
  line `made by him is exempt from tax or a refund or rebate of tax is admissible in respect thereof.]`
  line
  line `^2[(2A) Where is appears necessary to the authority to whom an application is made under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) so to do for the proper realisation of the tax payable under this Act or`
  line `for the proper custody and use of the forms referred to in clause (a) of the first proviso to sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 6 or sub-section (1) of section 6A or ^3[sub-section (4) of section 8], he may, by an order in`
  line `writing and for reasons to be recorded therein, impose as a condition for the issue of a certificate or`
  line `registration a requirement that the dealer shall furnish in the prescribed manner and within such time as`
  line `may be specified in the order such security as may be so specified, for all or any of the aforesaid`
  line purposes.]
  line
  line `(3) If the authority to whom an application under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) is made is`
  line `satisfied that the application is in conformity with the provisions of this Act and the rules made`
  line `thereunder ^2[and the condition, if any, imposed under sub-section (2A), has been complied with] he shall`
  line `register the applicant and grant to him a certificate of registration in the prescribed form which shall`
  line `specify the class or classes of goods for the purposes of sub-section (1) of section 8.`
  line
  line `^2[(3A) Where it appears necessary to the authority granting a certificate of registration under this`
  line `section so to do for the proper realisation of tax payable under this Act or for the proper custody and use`
  line `of the forms referred to in sub-section (3A), he may, at any time while such certificate is in force, by an`
  line `order in writing and for reasons to be recorded therein, require the dealer, to whom the certificate has`
  line `been granted, to furnish within such time as may be specified in the order and in the prescribed manner`
  line `such security, or, if the dealer has already furnished any security in pursuance of an order under this`
  line `sub-section or sub-section (2A), such additional security, as may be specified in the order, for all or any of`
  line `the aforesaid purposes.`
  line
  line `^4[(3B) No dealer shall be required to furnish any security and sub-section (2A) or any security or`
  line `additional security under sub-section (3A), unless he has been given an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(3BB) The amount of security which a dealer may be required to furnish under sub-section (2A) or`
  line `sub-section (3A) or the aggregate of the amount of such security and the amount of additional security`
  line `which may be required to furnish under sub-section (3A), by the authority referred to therein shall not`
  line exceed--
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a dealer other than a dealer who has made an application, or who has been`
  line `registered in pursuance of an application, under sub-section (2), a sum equal to the tax payable under`
  line `this Act, in accordance with the estimate of such authority, on the turnover of such dealer for the year`
  line `in which such security or, as the case may be, additional security is required to be furnished; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a dealer who has made an application, or who has been registered in pursuance`
  line `of an application, under sub-section (2), a sum equal to the tax leviable under this Act, in accordance`
  line `with the estimate of such authority on the sales to such dealer in the course of inter-State trade or`
  line `commerce in the year in which such security or, as the case may be additional security is required to`
  line `be furnished, had such dealer been not registered under this Act.]`
  line
  line `(3C) Where the security furnished by a dealer under sub-section (2A) or sub-section (3A) is in the`
  line `form of a surety bond and the surety becomes insolvent or dies, the dealer shall, within thirty days of the`
  line `occurrence of any of the aforesaid events, inform the authority granting the certificate of registration and`
  line `shall within ninety days of such occurrence furnish a fresh surety bond or furnish in the prescribed`
  line `manner other security for the amount of the bond.`
  line
  line `(3D) The authority granting the certificate of registration may by order and for good and sufficient`
  line `cause forfeit the whole or any part of the security furnished by a dealer,--`
  line
  line `(a) for realising any amount of tax or penalty payable by the dealer;`
  line
  line `(b) if the dealer is found to have misused any of the forms referred to in sub-section (2A) to have`
  line `failed to keep them in proper custody:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be passed under this sub-section without giving the dealer an opportunity`
  line `of being heard.`
  line
  line `(3E) Where by reason of an order under sub-section (3D), the security furnished by any dealer is`
  line `rendered insufficient, he shall make up the deficiency is such manner and within such time as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3F) The authority issuing the forms referred to in sub-section (2A) may refuse to issue such forms to`
  line `a dealer who has failed to comply with an order under that sub-section or sub-section (3A), or with the`
  line `provisions or sub-section (3C) or sub-section (3E), until the dealer has complied with such order or such`
  line `provisions, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3G) The authority granting a certificate of registration may, on application by the dealer to whom it`
  line `has been granted, order the refund of any amount or part thereof deposited by the dealer by way of`
  line `security under this section, if it is not required for the purpose of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3H) Any person aggrieved by an order passed under sub-section (2A), sub-section (3A),`
  line `sub-section (3D) or sub-section (3G) may, within thirty days of the service of the order on him, but after`
  line `furnishing the security, prefer, in such form and manner as may be prescribed, an appeal against such`
  line `order to such authority (here after in this section referred to as the "appellate authority") as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appellate authority may, for sufficient cause, permit such person to present the`
  line appeal,--
  line
  line `(a) after the expiry of the said period of thirty days; or`
  line
  line `(b) without furnishing the whole or any part of such security.`
  line
  line `(3-I) The procedure to be followed in hearing any appeal under sub-section (3H), and the fees payable`
  line `in respect of such appeals shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3J) The order passed by the appellate authority in any appeal under sub-section (3H) shall be final.`
  line
  line `^5[(4) A certificate of registration granted under this section may--`
  line
  line `(a) either on the application of the dealer to whom it has been granted or, where no such`
  line `application has been made, after due notice to the dealer, be amended by the authority granting it if he`
  line `is satisfied that by reason of the registered dealer having changed the name, place or nature of his`
  line `business or the class or classes of goods in which he carries on business or for any other reason the`
  line `certificate of registration granted to him requires to be amended; or`
  line
  line `(b) be cancelled by the authority granting it, where he is satisfied, after due notice to the dealer to`
  line `whom it has been granted, that he has ceased to carry on business ^6[or has ceased to exist or has failed`
  line `without sufficient cause, to comply with an order under sub-section (3A) or with the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (3C) or sub-section (3E) or has failed to pay any tax or penalty payable under this Act, or`
  line `in the case of a dealer registered under sub-section (2) has ceased to be liable to pay tax under the`
  line `sales tax of the appropriate State or for any other sufficient reason.]`
  line
  line `(5) A registered dealer may apply in the prescribed manner not later than six months before the end of`
  line `a year to the authority which granted his certificate of registration for the cancellation of such registration,`
  line `and the authority shall, unless the dealer is liable to pay tax under this Act, cancel the registration`
  line `accordingly, and where he does so, the cancellation shall take effect from the end of the year.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1958, s. 4, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 61 of 1972, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 16 of 2007, s. 3, for "clause (a) of sub-section (4) of section 8" (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 103 of 1976, s. 5, for sub-section (3B) (w.e.f. 7-9-1976).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 31 of 1958, s. 4, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 61 of 1972, s. 4, for "or has ceased to exist" (w.e.f. 1-4-1973)`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (33036)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Rates of tax on sales in the course of inter-State trade or commerce.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33036&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line ^1[
  line `^2[(1) Every dealer,`
  line `who in the course of inter-State trade or commence, sells to a registered dealer goods of the description`
  line `referred to in sub-section (3), shall be liable to pay tax under this Act, which shall be three per cent. of his`
  line `turnover or at the rate applicable to the sale or purchase of such goods inside the appropriate State under`
  line `the sales tax law of that State, whichever is lower:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, reduce the rate of`
  line `tax under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The tax payable by any dealer on his turnover in so far as the turnover or any part thereof relates`
  line `to the sale of goods in the course of inter-State trade or commerce not falling within sub-section (1), shall`
  line `be at the rate applicable to the sale or purchase of such goods inside the appropriate State under the sales`
  line `tax law of that State.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, a dealer shall be deemed to be a dealer liable to`
  line `pay tax under the sales tax law of the appropriate State, notwithstanding that he, in fact, may not be so`
  line `liable under that law.`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) ^4[The goods referred to in sub-section (1),--]`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `^6[(b) are goods of the class or classes specified in the certificate of registration of the registered dealer purchasing the goods as being intended for re-sale by him or subject to any rules made by the Central Government in this behalf, for use by him in the manufacture or processing for sale of goods specified under clause (d) of section 2;]`
  line
  line `(c) are containers or other materials specified in the certificate of registration of the registered`
  line `dealer purchasing the goods, being containers or materials intended for being used for the packing of`
  line `goods for sale;`
  line
  line `(d) are containers or other materials used for the packing of any goods or classes of goods`
  line `specified in the certificate of registration referred to in ^7*** clause (b) or for the packing of any`
  line `containers or other materials specified in the certificate of registration referred to in clause (c).`
  line
  line `^8[(4) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply to any sale in the course of inter-State trade or`
  line `commerce unless the dealer selling the goods furnishes to the prescribed authority in the prescribed`
  line `manner a declaration duly filled and signed by the registered dealer to whom the goods are sold`
  line `containing the prescribed particulars in a prescribed form obtained from the prescribed authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that the declaration is furnished within the prescribed time or within such further time as`
  line `that authority may, for sufficient cause, permit.]]`
  line
  line `^9[(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, the State Government may,`
  line `^10[on the`
  line `fulfillment of the requirements laid down in sub-section (4) by the dealer,] if it is satisfied that it is`
  line `necessary so to do in the public interest, by notification in the Official Gazette and subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be specified therein direct,--`
  line
  line `(a) that no tax under this Act shall be payable by any dealer having his place of business in the`
  line `State in respect of the sales by him, in the course of inter-State trade or commerce ^10[to a registered`
  line `dealer ^11***], from any such place of business of any such goods or classes of goods as may be`
  line `specified in the notification, or that the tax on such sales shall be calculated at such lower rates than`
  line `those specified in sub-section (1)`
  line `^11*** as may be mentioned in the notification;`
  line
  line `(b) that in respect of all sales of goods or sales of such classes of goods as may by specified in the`
  line `notification, which are made, in the course of inter-State trade or commerce ^10[to a registered`
  line `dealer ^11***], by any dealer having his place of business in the State or by any class of such dealers as`
  line `may be specified in the notification to any person or to such class of persons as may be specified in`
  line `the notification, no tax under this Act shall be payable or the tax on such sales shall be calculated at`
  line `such lower rates than those specified in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) ^11*** as may be mentioned`
  line `in the notification.`
  line
  line `^12[(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, no tax under this Act shall be payable by`
  line `any dealer in respect of sale of any goods made by such dealer, in the course of inter-State trade or`
  line `commerce to a registered dealer for the purpose of setting up, operation, maintenance, manufacture,`
  line `trading, production, processing, assembling, repairing, reconditioning, re-engineering, packaging or for`
  line `use as packing material or packing accessories in a unit located in any special economic zone or for`
  line `development, operation and maintenance of special economic zone by the developer of the special`
  line
  line `economic zone, if such registered dealer has been authorised to establish such unit or to develop, operate`
  line `and maintain such special economic zone by the authority specified by the Central Government in this`
  line behalf.]
  line
  line `(7) The goods referred to in sub-section (6) shall be the goods of such class or classes of goods as`
  line `specified in the certificate of registration of the registered dealer referred to in that sub-section.`
  line
  line `(8) The provisions of sub-sections (6) and (7) shall not apply to any sale of goods made in the course`
  line `of inter-State trade or commerce unless the dealer selling such goods furnishes to the ^13`
  line prescribed
  line `authority referred to in sub-section (4) a declaration in the prescribed manner on the prescribed form`
  line `obtained from the authority specified by the Central Government under sub-section (6) duly filled in and`
  line `signed by the registered dealer to whom such goods are sold.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of sub-section (6), the expression special economic zone has the`
  line `meaning assigned to it in clause (iii) to Explanation 2 to the proviso to section 3 of the Central Excise`
  line `Act, 1944 (1 of 1944).]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1958, s. 5, for sub-sections (1), (2), (3) and (4) (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2007, s. 4, for sub-sections (1) and (2) (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (2A) omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 150 (w.e.f. 13-5-2002).`
  line
  line `4 Subs. by Act 16 of 2007, s. 4, for The goods referred to in clauses (b) of sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line
  line `5. Cl. (a) omitted by Act 8 of 1963, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 150, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `7. The words, brackets and letter clause (a) or omitted by Act 8 of 1963, s. 150 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 16 of 2007, s. 4, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 61 of 1972, s. 5, for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 152 (w.e.f. 13-5-2002).`
  line
  line `11. The words or the Government omitted by Act 16 of 2007, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 118, for sub-section (6) (w.e.f. 10-09-2004).`
  line
  line `13. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 118, for certain words (w.e.f. 10-9-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (33037)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 10
  title `Determination of turnover.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 1969, s. 5 (retrospectively).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33037&sectionno=8A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[8A. Determination of turnover.--(1) In determining the turnover of a dealer for the purposes of`
  line `this Act, the following deductions shall be made from the aggregate of the sale prices, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount arrived at by applying the following formula--`
  line
  line `rate of tax x aggregate of sale prices :`
  line
  line ________________________________________________________
  line
  line `100 plus rate of tax`
  line
  line `Provided that no deduction on the basis of the above formula shall be made if the amount by way`
  line `of tax collected by a registered dealer, in accordance with the provisions of this Act, has been`
  line `otherwise deducted from the aggregate of sale prices.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Where the turnover of a dealer is taxable at different rates, the aforesaid formula`
  line `shall be applied separately in respect of each part of the turnover liable to a different rates of tax;`
  line
  line `(b) the sale price of all goods returned to the dealer by the purchasers of such goods,--`
  line
  line `(i) within a period of three months from the date of delivery of the goods, in the case`
  line `of goods returned before the 14th day of May, 1966;`
  line
  line `(ii) within a period of six months from the date of delivery of the goods, in the case of goods`
  line `returned on or after the 14th day of may, 1966:`
  line
  line `Provided that satisfactory evidence of such return of goods and of refund or adjustment in`
  line `accounts of the sale price thereof is produced before the authority competent to assess or, as the case`
  line `may be, re-assess the tax payable by the dealer under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(c) such other deductions as the Central Government may, having regard to the prevalent`
  line `market conditions, facility of trade and interests of consumers, prescribe.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (1), in determining the turn over of a dealer for the`
  line `purposes of this Act, no deduction shall be made from the aggregate of the sale prices.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (33038)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 11
  title `Levy and collection of tax and penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33038&sectionno=9&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line ^1[
  line `^2[9. Levy and collection of tax and penalties.--(1) The tax payable by any dealer under this Act`
  line `on sales of goods effected by him in the course of inter-State trade or commerce, whether such sales fall`
  line `within clause (a) or clause (b) of section 3, shall be levied by the Government of India and the tax so`
  line `levied shall be collected by that Government in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2), in the`
  line `State from which the movement of the goods commenced:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that, in the case of a sale of goods during their movement from one State of another, being`
  line `a sale subsequent to the first sale in respect of the same goods and being also a sale which does not fall`
  line `within sub-section (2) of section 6, the tax shall be levied and collected--`
  line
  line `(a) where such subsequent sale has been effected by a registered dealer, in the State from which`
  line `the registered dealer obtained or, as the case may be, could have obtained, the form prescribed for the`
  line `purpose of ^4[sub-section (4) of section 8] in connection with the purchase of such goods, and`
  line
  line `(b) where such subsequent sale has been effected by an unregistered dealer in the State from`
  line `which such subsequent sale has been effected.]`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the other provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, the authorities for the`
  line `time being empowered to assess, re-assess, collect and enforce payment of any tax under the general sales`
  line `tax law of the appropriate State shall, on behalf of the Government of India, assess re-assess, collect and`
  line `enforce payment of tax, including any ^5[interest or penalty,] payable by a dealer under this Act as if the`
  line `tax or ^5[interest or penalty] payable by such a dealer under this Act is a tax or ^5[interest or penalty]`
  line `payable under the general sales tax law of the State; and for this purpose they may exercise all or any of`
  line `the powers they have under the general sales tax law of the State; and the provisions of such law,`
  line `including provisions relating to returns, provisional assessment, advance payment of tax, registration of`
  line `the transferee of any business, imposition of the tax liability of a person carrying on business on the`
  line `transfer of, or successor to, such business, transfer of liability of any firm of Hindu undivided family to`
  line `pay tax in the event of the dissolution of such firm or partition of such family, recovery of tax from third`
  line `parties, appeals, reviews, provisions, references, ^6[refunds, rebated, penalties,] ^5[interest or penalty]]`
  line `^7[charging or payment of interest,] compounding of offences and treatment of documents furnished by a`
  line `dealer as confidential, shall apply accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that if in any State or part thereof there is no general sales tax law in force, the Central`
  line `Government may, be rules made in this behalf make necessary provision for all or any of the matter`
  line `specified in this sub-section.`
  line
  line `^7[(2A) All the ^8[provisions relating to offences, interest and penalties] (including provisions relating to`
  line `penalties in lieu of prosecution for an offence or in addition to the penalties or punishment for an offence`
  line `but excluding the provisions relating to matters provided for in section 10 and 10A) of the general sales`
  line `tax law of each State shall, with necessary modifications, apply in relation to the assessment,`
  line `re-assessment, collection and the enforcement of payment of any tax required to be collected under this`
  line `Act in such State or in relation to any process connected with such assessment, re-assessment, collection`
  line `or enforcement of payment as if the tax under this Act were a tax under such sales tax law.]`
  line
  line `^9[(2B) If the tax payable by any dealer under this Act is not paid in time, the dealer shall be liable to`
  line `pay interest for delayed payment of such tax and all the provisions for delayed payment of such tax and`
  line `all the provisions relating to due date for payment of tax, rate of interest for delayed payment of tax and`
  line `assessment and collection of interest for delayed payment of tax, of the general sales tax law of each`
  line `State, shall apply in relation to due date for payment of tax, rate of interest for delayed payment of tax,`
  line `and assessment and collection of interest for delayed payment of tax under this Act in such States as if the`
  line `tax and the interest payable under this Act were a tax and an interest under such sales tax law.]`
  line
  line `(3) The proceeds in any financial year of any tax, ^10[including any interest or penalty] levied and`
  line `collected under this Act in any State (other than a Union territory) on behalf on the Government of India`
  line `shall be assigned to the State and shall be retained by it; and the proceeds attributable to Union territories`
  line `shall form part of the Consolidated Fund of India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1958, s. 6, for the original section 9 (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 1969, s. 6, for section 9 (retrospectively).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso subs. by Act 103 of 1976, s. 6 (w.e.f. 7-9-1976).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 16 of 2007, s. 5, for "clause (a) of sub-section (4) of section 8" (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 119, for "penalty" (w.e.f. 12-5-2000).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 61 of 1972, s. 6, for "refunds, penalties" (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 103 of 1976, s. 6 (retrospectively).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 119, for "provisions relating to offences and penalties" (w.e.f. 12-5-2000).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by s. 119, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-5-2000).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 119, for "including any penalty" (w.e.f. 12-5-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (33039)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 12
  title `Collection of tax to be only by registered dealers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1958, s. 6, for the original section 9 (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33039&sectionno=9A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[9A. Collection of tax to be only by registered dealers.--No person who is not a registered dealer`
  line `shall collect in respect of any sale by him of goods in the course of Inter-State trade or commerce any`
  line `amount by way of tax under this Act, and no registered dealer shall make may such collection except in`
  line `accordance with this Act and the rules made thereunder.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_b:
  sectionId (33040)
  sectionNo 9B
  orderNo 13
  title `Rounding off of tax, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 61 of 1972, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33040&sectionno=9B&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_9_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[9B. Rounding off of tax, etc.--The amount of tax, penalty, fine or any other sum payable, and the`
  line `amount of refund due, under the provisions of this Act shall be rounded off to the nearest rupees and, for`
  line `the purpose, where such amount contains a part of a rupee consisting of paise, then, if such part is fifty`
  line `paise or more, it shall be increased to one rupee and if such part is less than fifty paise, it shall be ignored:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply for the purpose of collection by a dealer of any`
  line `amount by way of tax under this Act in respect of any sale by him of goods in the course of inter-State`
  line `trade or commerce.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (33041)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 14
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33041&sectionno=10&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `If any person--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) furnishes a ^2*** declaration under sub-section (2) of section 6 or sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 6A or sub-section (4)`
  line `^3[sub-section (8)] which he knows, or has reason to believe, to be false;`
  line
  line or
  line
  line `(aa) fails to get himself registered as required by section 7 or fails to comply with an order under`
  line `sub-section (3A) or with the requirements of sub-section (3C) or sub-section (3E) of that section;`
  line
  line `(b) being a registered dealer, falsely represents when purchasing any class of goods that goods of`
  line `such class are covered by his certificate of registration; or`
  line
  line `(c) not being a registered dealer, falsely represents when purchasing goods in the course of`
  line `inter- State trade or commerce that he is a registered dealer; or`
  line
  line `(d) after purchasing any goods for any of the purposes specified in ^4[clause (b) or clause (c) or`
  line `clause (d)] of sub- section (3)`
  line `^3[or sub-section (6)] of section 8 fails, without reasonable excuse, to`
  line `make use of the goods for any such purpose;`
  line
  line `(e) has in his possession any form prescribed for the purpose of sub-section (4)`
  line `^3[or sub-section (8)] of section 8 which has not been obtained by him or by his principal or by his`
  line `agent in accordance with the provisions of this Act or any rules made there under;`
  line
  line `^5[(f) collects any amount by way of tax in contravention of the provisions contained in`
  line `section 9A,]`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with simple imprisonment which may extend to six months, or with fine or with`
  line `both, and when the offence is a continuing offence, with a daily fine which may extend to fifty rupees for`
  line `every day during which the offence continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line
  line `2. The words "certificate or" omitted by Act 16 of 2007, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-04-2007).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 153 (w.e.f. 13-05-2002).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 61 of 1972, s. 8, for "clause (b)" (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 31 of 1958, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (33042)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 15
  title `Imposition of penalty in lieu of prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33042&sectionno=10A&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Imposition of penalty in lieu of prosecution.--, ^2[(1)] If any person purchasing goods is`
  line `guilty of an offence under clause (b) or clause (c) or clause (d) of section 10, the authority who granted to`
  line `him or, as the case may be, is competent to grant to him a certificate of registration under this Act may,`
  line `after giving him a reasonable opportunity of being heard, by order in writing impose upon him by way of`
  line `penalty a sum not exceeding one-and-a-half times ^3[the tax which would have been levied under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 8 in respect of the sale to him of the goods, if the sale had been a sale falling`
  line `within that sub-section]:`
  line
  line `Provided that no prosecution for an offence under section 10 shall be instituted in respect of the same`
  line `facts on which a penalty has been imposed under this section.`
  line
  line `^4[(2) The penalty imposed upon any dealer under sub-section (1) shall be collected by the`
  line `Government of India in the manner provided in sub-section (2) of section 9--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an offence falling under clause (b) or clause (d) of section 10, in the State in`
  line `which the person purchasing the goods obtained the form prescribed for the purposes of ^5[sub-section`
  line `(4) of section 8] in connection with the purchase of such goods;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an offence falling under clause (c) of section 10, in the State in which the person`
  line `purchasing the goods should have registered himself if the offence had not been committed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 1958, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `2. Section 10A re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 28 of 1969, s. 7 (w.r.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 61 of 1972, s.9, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 28 of 1969, section 7 (w.r.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 16 of 2007, s. 5, for "clause (a) of sub-section (4) of section 8" (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (33043)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 16
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33043&sectionno=11&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under`
  line `this Act or the rules made thereunder except with the previous sanction of the Government within the`
  line `local limits of whose jurisdiction the offence has been committed or of such officer of that Government as`
  line `it may, by general or special order, specify in this behalf; and no court inferior to that of a presidency`
  line `magistrate or a magistrate of the first class shall try and such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) All offences punishable under this Act shall be cognizable and bailable.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (33044)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 17
  title Indemnity.
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33044&sectionno=12&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie against any officer of`
  line `Government for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules`
  line `made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (33045)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33045&sectionno=13&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules providing for--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which applications for registration may be made under this Act, the particulars`
  line `to be contained therein, the procedure for the grant of such registration, the circumstances in which`
  line `registration may be refused and the form in which the certificate of registration may be given;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) the manner of determination of the sale price and the deduction from the total consideration`
  line `for a works contract under the proviso to clause (h) of section 2;]`
  line
  line `^2[(ab) the form and the manner for furnishing declaration under sub-section (8) of section 8;]`
  line
  line `(b) the period turnover, the manner in which the turnover in relation to the sale of any goods`
  line `under this Act shall be determined, and the deductions which may be made ^3[under clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 8A] in the process of such determination;`
  line
  line `(c) the cases and circumstances in which, and the conditions subject to which, any`
  line `registration granted under this Act may be cancelled;`
  line
  line `^4[(d) the form in which and the particulars to be contained in the declaration or certificate to be`
  line `given under this Act ^3[the State of origin or such form or certificate and the time within which any`
  line `such certificate or declaration shall be produced or furnished];`
  line
  line `(e) the enumeration of goods or class of goods used in the manufacture or processing of goods for`
  line `sale or in mining or in the generation or distribution of electricity or any other form of power;`
  line
  line `(f) the matters in respect of which provision may be made under the provision to ^5[sub-section`
  line `(2)] of section 9;`
  line
  line `(g) the fees payable in respect of applications under this Act.]`
  line
  line `^6[(h) the proper functioning of the Authority constituted under section 19;`
  line
  line `(i) the salaries and allowances payable to, and the terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Chairman and Members under sub-section (3) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `^7[(2) Every rule made by the Central Government under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may`
  line `be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.]`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may make rules, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act and the`
  line `rules made under sub-section (1), to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) In particular and without prejudice to the powers conferred by sub-section (3), the State`
  line `Government may make rules for all or any of the following purposes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the publication of lists of registered dealers, of the amendments made in such lists from time`
  line `to time, and the particulars to be contained in such lists;`
  line
  line `^8[(aa) the manner in which security may be furnished under sub-section (2A) or`
  line `sub-section (3A) or sub-section (3C) of section 7 and the manner in which and the time within which`
  line `any deficiency may be made up under sub-section (3E) of that section;]`
  line
  line `(b) the form and manner in which accounts relating to sales in the course of inter-State trade`
  line `or commerce shall be kept by registered dealers;`
  line
  line `(c) the furnishing of any information relating to the stocks of goods of, purchases, sales`
  line `and deliveries of books by, any dealer or any other information relating to his business as may`
  line `be necessary for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) the inspection of any books, accounts or documents required to be kept under this Act, the entry`
  line `into any premises at all reasonable times for the purposes of searching for any such books, accounts or`
  line `documents kept or suspected to be kept in such premises and the seizure of such books, accounts or`
  line documents;
  line
  line `^9[(e) the authority from whom, the conditions subject to which and fees subject to payment`
  line `of which any form of certificate prescribed under clause (a) of the first proviso to sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 6 or of declaration prescribed under sub-section (1) of section 6A or sub-section (4) of section 8`
  line `may be obtained, the manner in which such forms shall be kept in custody and records relating thereto`
  line `maintained and the manner in which any such form may be used and any such certificate or declaration`
  line `may be furnished;`
  line
  line `(ee) the form and manner in which, and the authority to whom, an appeal may be preferred`
  line `under sub-section (3H) of section 7, the procedure to be followed in hearing such appeals and the fees`
  line `payable in respect of such appeals;]`
  line
  line `(f) in the case of an undivided Hindu Family, association, club, society, firm or company or in the`
  line `case of a person who carries on business as a guardian or trustee or otherwise on behalf of another`
  line `person, the furnishing of a declaration stating the name of the person who shall be deemed to be the`
  line `manager in relation to the business of the dealer in the State and the form in which such declaration`
  line `may be given;`
  line
  line `(g) the time within which, the manner in which and ^10[the authorities to whom] any change in the`
  line `ownership of any business or in ^11[the name, place or nature] of any business carried on by any dealer`
  line `shall be furnished.`
  line
  line `(5) In making any rule under this section ^12[the Central Government or, as the case may be, the State`
  line `Government] may direct that a breach thereof shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five`
  line `hundred rupees and when the offence is a continuing offence, with a daily fine which may extend to fifty`
  line `rupees for every day during which the offence continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 92 (w.e.f. 13-5-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (aa) lettered as clause (ab) thereof by s. 92, ibid. (w.e.f. 13-5-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 61 of 1972, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 31 of 1958, s. 9, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 28 of 1969, s. 8, for "sub-section (3)" (retrospectively).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 41 of 2001, s. 2 (w.e.f. 17-3-2005).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 61 of 1972, s. 10, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line
  line `9 Subs. by Act 61 of 1972, s.10, for clause (e) (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 31 of 1958, s. 9, for "the authorities to which" ( w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 31 of 1953, s. 9, for "the nature" (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by Act 61 of 1972, s.10, for "the State Government" (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
