obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `[Restrictions and conditions in regard to tax on sales or purchases of declared goods.] Omitted by`
  line `s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (33048)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 21
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f 1-4-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33048&sectionno=16&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[16. Definitions.--In this Chapter,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appropriate authority", in relation to a company, means the authority competent to assess`
  line `tax on the company;`
  line
  line `(b) "company" and "private company" have the meanings respectively assigned to them by`
  line `clauses (i) and (iii) of sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (33049)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 22
  title `Company in liquidation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f 1-4-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33049&sectionno=17&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `^1[17. Company in liquidation.--(1) Every person--`
  line
  line `(a) who is the liquidator of any company which is being wound up, whether under the orders of`
  line `a court or otherwise; or`
  line
  line `(b) who has been appointed the receiver of any assets of a company, hereinafter referred to as`
  line `the liquidator shall, within thirty days after he has become such liquidator, give notice of`
  line `his appointment as such to the appropriate authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate authority shall, after making such inquiry of calling for such information as it`
  line `may deem fit, notify to the liquidator within three months form the date on which he receives notice of the`
  line `appointment of the liquidator the amount which, in the opinion of the appropriate authority would be`
  line `sufficient to provide for any tax which is then, or is likely thereafter to become, payable by the company.`
  line
  line `(3) The liquidator shall not part with any of the assets of the company or the properties in his hands`
  line `until he has been notified by the appropriate authority under sub-section (2) and no being so notified, shall`
  line `set aside an amount equal to the amount notified and, until he so sets aside such amount, shall not part`
  line `with any of the assets of the company or the properties in his hands:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall debar the liquidator from parting with such`
  line `assets or properties in compliance with any order of a court or for the purpose of the payment of the tax`
  line `payable by the company under this Act or for making any payment to secured creditors whose debts are`
  line `entitled under law to priority of payment over debts due to Government on the date of liquidation or for`
  line `meeting such costs and expenses of the winding up of the company as are in the opinion of the`
  line `appropriate authority reasonable.`
  line
  line `(4) If the liquidator fails to give the notice in accordance with sub-section (1) or fails or set aside the`
  line `amount as required by, or parts with any of the assets of the company or the properties in his hands in`
  line `contravention of the provisions of sub-section (3), he shall be personally liable for the payment of the tax`
  line `which the company would be liable to pay:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the amount of any tax payable by the company is notified under sub-section (2), the`
  line `personal liability of the liquidator under this sub-section shall be to the extent of such amount.`
  line
  line `(5) Where there are more liquidators than one, the obligations and liabilities attached to the liquidator`
  line `under this section shall attach to all the liquidators jointly and severally.`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of this section shall have effect notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained`
  line `in any other law for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (33050)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 23
  title `Liability of directors of private company in liquidation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f 1-4-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33050&sectionno=18&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `^1[18. Liability of directors of private company in liquidation.--Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), when any private company is wound up after the commencement`
  line `of this Act, and any tax assessed on the company under this Act for any period, whether before or in the`
  line `course of or after its liquidation, cannot be recovered, then, every person who was a director of the private`
  line `company at any time during the period for which the tax is due shall be jointly and severally liable for the`
  line `payment of such tax unless he proves that the non-recovery cannot be attributed to any gross neglect,`
  line `misfeasance or breach of duty on his part in relation to the affairs of company.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_a:
  sectionId (33051)
  sectionNo 18A
  orderNo 24
  title `Appeals to highest appellate authority of State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33051&sectionno=18A&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[18A. Appeals to highest appellate authority of State.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in a`
  line `State Act, any person aggrieved by an order made by the assessing authority under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 6A, or an order made under the provisions of sub-section (3) of that section, may, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the general sales tax law of the appropriate State, prefer an appeal to the highest`
  line `appellate authority of the State against such order:`
  line
  line `Provided that any incidental issues including the rate of tax, computation of assessable turnover and`
  line `penalty may be raised in such appeal.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within sixty days from the date^2`
  line `on which the order`
  line `referred to in that sub-section is communicated to the aggrieved person:`
  line
  line `Provided that any appeal forwarded by the highest appellate authority of a State to the first appellate`
  line `authority under the proviso to sub-section (2) of section 25 and pending before such authority`
  line `immediately before the appointed day shall be transferred, on such appointed day, to the highest appellate`
  line `authority of the State and the same shall be treated as an appeal filed under sub-section (1) and dealt with`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "appointed day" means such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint.`
  line
  line `(3) The highest appellate authority of a State may, after giving both the parties an opportunity of`
  line `being heard, pass appropriate order.`
  line
  line `(4) The highest appellate authority of the State may, as far as practicable, hear and decide such appeal`
  line `within a period of six months from the date of filing of the appeal.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in a State Act, the highest appellate authority of a State may,`
  line `on the application of the appellant and after considering relevant facts, including the deposit of any`
  line `amount towards local or central sales tax in other States on the same goods, pass an order of stay subject`
  line `to such terms and conditions as it thinks fit, and such order may, inter alia, indicate the portion of tax as`
  line `assessed, to be deposited prior to admission of the appeal.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section and sections 20, 21, 22 and 25, "highest appellate`
  line `authority of a State", with its grammatical variations, means any authority or tribunal or court, except the`
  line `High Court, established or constituted under the general sales tax law of a State, by whatever name`
  line called.]
obj_root_law_sections_18_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 79 (w.e.f. 1-6-2010).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 41 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f. 17-3-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (33052)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 25
  title `Central Sales Tax Appellate Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33052&sectionno=19&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^1[19. Central Sales Tax Appellate Authority.--(1) The Central Government constitute, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, an Authority to settle inter-State disputes falling under ^2[section 6A`
  line `read with section 9] of this Act, to be known as "the Central Sales Tax Appellate Authority (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the Authority").`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall consist of the following Members appointed by the Central Government,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman, who is a retired Judge of the Supreme Court, or a retired Chief Justice of a High`
  line Court;
  line
  line `(b) an officer of the Indian Legal Service who is, or is qualified to be, an Additional Secretary to`
  line `the Government of India; and`
  line
  line `(c) an officer of a State Government not below the rank of Secretary or an officer of the Central`
  line `Government not below the rank of Additional Secretary, who is an expert in sales tax matters.`
  line
  line `^3[(2A)Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the Chairman or a Member holding a`
  line `post as such in the Authority for Advance Rulings appointed under clause (a) or clause (c), as the case`
  line `may be, of sub-section (2) of section 245-O of the Income-tax Act,1961 (43 of 1961) may, in addition to`
  line `his being the Chairman or a Member of that Authority, be appointed as the Chairman or a Member, as the`
  line `case may be, of the Authority under this Act.]`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the terms and conditions of service of, the Chairman`
  line `and Members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall provide the Authority with such officers and staff as may be`
  line `necessary for the efficient exercise of the powers of the Authority under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f. 17-3-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 119, for "section 6A or section 9" (w.e.f. 10-9-2004).`
  line
  line `3 Ins. by Act 3 of 2006, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-3-2006)`
obj_root_law_sections_19_a:
  sectionId (33053)
  sectionNo 19A
  orderNo 26
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33053&sectionno=19A&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^2[19A. Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings.No proceeding before the Authority shall be`
  line `questioned or shall be invalid on the ground merely of the existence of any vacancy or defect in the`
  line `constitution of the Authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f. 17-3-2005)`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-3-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (33054)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 27
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33054&sectionno=20&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^2[20. Appeals.-- ^3`
  line `[(1) An appeal shall lie to the Authority against any order passed by the highest`
  line `appellate authority of a State under this Act determining issues relating to stock transfers or consignments`
  line `of goods, in so far as they involve a dispute of inter-State nature.]`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the general sales tax law of a State, the Authority shall`
  line `adjudicate an appeal filed under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) An appeal under sub-section (1) may be filed within ninety days from the date on which the order`
  line `referred to in that sub-section is served on any aggrieved person:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority may entertain any appeal after the expiry of the said period of ninety`
  line `days, but not later than one hundred and fifty days from the date of such service, if it is satisfied that the`
  line `appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in time:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Authority may entertain any appeal from an aggrieved person within sixty`
  line `days from the commencement of the Central Sales Tax (Amendment) Act, 2005 (3 of 2006), where such`
  line `aggrieved person had the right to file an appeal against the order of the highest appellate authority of the`
  line `State under sub-section (1) as it stood immediately before the commencement of the said Act, but has not`
  line `availed of the right to file the appeal during the period commencing on and from the 3rd day of`
  line `December, 2001 and ending with the 16th day of March, 2005.`
  line
  line `(4) The application shall be made in quadruplicate and be accompanied by a fee of five thousand`
  line rupees].]
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f. 17-3-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for section 20 (w.e.f. 1-3-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 80, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 8-5-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (33055)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 28
  title `Procedure on receipt of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33055&sectionno=21&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of an appeal, the Authority shall cause a`
  line `copy thereof to be forwarded to the ^1[assessing appellate authority] concerned as well as to each State`
  line `Government concerned with the appeal and to call upon them to furnish the relevant records:`
  line
  line `Provided that such records shall, as soon as possible, be returned to the ^2[highest authority] or such`
  line `State Government concerned, as the case may be].`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall adjudicate and decide upon the appeal filed against an order of the ^2[highest`
  line authority].
  line
  line `(3) The Authority, after examining the appeal and the records called for, by order, either allow or`
  line `reject the appeal:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that no appeal shall be rejected unless an opportunity has been given to the appellant of`
  line `being heard in person or through a duly authorised representative, and ^4[also to each State Government]`
  line `concerned with the appeal of being heard.]`
  line
  line `Provided further that whether an appeal is rejected or accepted, reasons for such rejection or`
  line `acceptance shall be given in the order.`
  line
  line `(4) The Authority shall make an endeavour to pronounce its order in writing within six months of the`
  line `receipt of the appeal.`
  line
  line `(5) A copy of every order made under sub-section (3) shall be sent to the ^5[appellant, assessing`
  line `authority, respondent and highest appellate authority of the State Government concerned.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 164, for certain words (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 2006, s. 5, for "assessing authority" (w.e.f. 1-3-2006).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s.164 (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 119, for "also to the State Government" (w.e.f. 10-9-2004).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 3 of 2006, s. 5, for "appellant and to the assessing authority" (w.e.f. 1-3-2006)`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (33056)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 29
  title `Poweres of the Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33056&sectionno=22&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^1[22. Poweres of the Authority.--(1) The Authority shall have the same powers as are vested in a`
  line `court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) enforcing the attendance of any person, examining him on oath or affirmation;`
  line
  line `(b) compelling the production of accounts and documents;`
  line
  line `(c) issuing commission for the examination of witnesses;`
  line
  line `(d) the reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) The Authority may grant stay of the operation of the order of the highest appellate authority`
  line `against which the appeal is filed before it or order the ^3[deposit] of the tax before entertaining the appeal`
  line `and while granting such stay or making such order for the ^3[deposit] of the tax, the Authority shall have`
  line `regard, if the assessee has made ^3[deposit] of the tax under the general sales tax law of the State`
  line `concerned, to such ^3[deposit] or pass such appropriate order as it may deem fit.]`
  line
  line `^4[(1B) The Authority may issue direction for refund of tax collected by a State which has been held`
  line `by the Authority to be not due to that State, or alternatively, direct that State to transfer the refundable`
  line `amount to the State to which central sales tax is due on the same transaction:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount of tax directed to be refunded by a State shall not exceed the amount of`
  line `central sales tax payable by the appellant on the same transaction.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every proceeding before the Authority shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of section 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code and the Authority shall be deemed to be a civil`
  line `court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of`
  line `1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f. 17-3-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for sub-section (1A) (w.e.f. 1-3-2006).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 81, for "pre-deposit" (w.e.f. 8-5-2010).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 81 (w.e.f. 8-5-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (33057)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 30
  title `Procedure of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33057&sectionno=23&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `^1[23. Procedure of Authority.--The Authority shall, subject to the provisions of this Chapter, have`
  line `power to regulate its own procedure ^2[in all matters, including stay of recovery of any demand] arising out`
  line `of the exercise of powers under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f. 17-3-2005).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 165, for "in all matters" (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (33058)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 31
  title `Authority for Advance Ruilings to function as Authority under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f. 17-3-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33058&sectionno=24&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `^1[24. Authority for Advance Ruilings to function as Authority under this Act.--(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force and in section 19 of this`
  line `Act, the Authority for Advance Rulings constituted under section 245-O of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43`
  line `of 1961) shall be notified by the Central Government in the Official Gazette, with such modifications as`
  line `many be necessary, to make its composition in conformity with section 19 of this Act, as the Authority`
  line `under this Act till such time an Authority is constituted under that section.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the date of the constitution of the Authority in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `section 19 of this Act, the proceedings pending with the Authority for Advance Rulings shall stand`
  line `transferred to the Authority constituted under that section from the stage at which such proceedings stood`
  line `before the date of constitution of the said Authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (33059)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 32
  title `Transfer of pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33059&sectionno=25&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^2[25. Transfer of pending proceedings.--(1) On and from the commencement of the Central Sales`
  line `Tax (Amendment) Act, 2005 (3 of 2006), all appeals (except appeals against orders of the highest`
  line `appellate authority of the State) pending before the Authority notified under sub-section (1) of section 24`
  line `shall stand transferred together with the records thereof to the highest appellate authority of the concerned`
  line State.
  line
  line `(2) Such highest appellate authority of the State to which such appeal has been transferred under sub-section (1) on receipt of such records shall proceed to deal with such appeal so far as may be in the same manner as in the case of an appeal filed before such highest appellate authority of the State according to the general sales tax law of the appropriate State, from the stage which was reached before such transfer or from any earlier stage or de novo as such highest appellate authority of the State may deem fit:`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f. 17-3-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 2006, s. 7, for section 25 (w.e.f. 1-3-2006).`
  line
  line `3. Proviso to Sub-section (2) omitted by Act 14 of 2010, s. 82 (w.e.f. 8-5-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (33060)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 33
  title `Applicability of order passed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884&sectionId=33060&sectionno=26&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00044_195674_1538559878884
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `^1[26. Applicability of order passed.-- An order passed by the Authority under this Chapter shall be`
  line `binding on`
  line `^2[each State Government concerned, the assessing authorities] and other authorities created by`
  line `or under any law relating to general sales tax, in force for the time being in any State ^3***.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2006, s. 7, for section 25 (w.e.f. 1-3-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 119, for "the assessing authorities" (w.e.f. 10-9-2004).`
  line
  line `3. The words "or Union territory" omitted by Act 3 of 2006, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-3-2006).`
